main event: A round object with a number of points was observed visually for 35 minutes in Fountain, Colorado on August 22, 1956.
interesting points: The object was much brighter than a star and had the same color.
The object was initially sighted at approximately 90 degrees elevation.
The object disappeared after 33 minutes, leaving a trail.
The characteristics of the sighting were similar to those of a star or planet, possibly Venus.
The observation was made by a civilian and recorded in a Project Blue Book record card.
result: likely a star or planet, possibly Venus
sighted object: a round object with a number of points
